INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES("253", "1", "2017-05-17 08:27:53", "2017-05-17 08:27:53", "<strong>Welcome to The Whole Food Nut!</strong>\r\n<table style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"float: right; width: 50%; text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-word;\">I’m a Nutritionist &amp; Whole Food Nut that wants to help others overcome the hurdles to eating healthy. Thru educational videos, nutrition tips &amp; the Facebook page, I’ll share the health benefits of preparing &amp; eating whole foods. People are overwhelmed with the mass amount of conflicting &amp; rapidly changing nutrition data. I want to simplify &amp; break down the challenges to healthy eating as well as provide wellness &amp; nutrition tips to incorporate into your daily life. I’m not a fan of fad diets that promote one way of eating over another because every person has different nutritive needs that are based upon their biochemical individuality. Healthy eating is a balance of moderation &amp; variation not deprivation. There’s so many foods to discover, eat &amp; enjoy!</td>\r\n<td style=\"float: left; width: 50%; text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-word;\"><img class=\"wp-image-183 aligncenter\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/food-nut/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/Butterfly-pic-300x170.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"100%\" height=\"100%\" /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<strong>Whole Food Nut Tips</strong>\r\n<table style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"float: right; width: 50%; text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-word;\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-154 size-medium\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/food-nut/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/Picture1-261x300.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"85%\" height=\"85%\" /></td>\r\n<td style=\"float: left; width: 50%; text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-word;\">Where do I begin? What should I eat? What the heck is a whole food? After hearing these questions asked over &amp; over, I reflected on my food journey &amp; realized the need for food education. We are not taught in school one of the most important things in life; what &amp; how to eat. It\'s not pretty when I reflect on my initial attempts at cooking &amp; learning what to eat. Lesson #1 This doesn\'t happen overnight. Be patient, have a good sense of humor &amp; embrace your kitchen as a science experiment! Lesson #2 Do not start with fancyschmancy recipes because that will only add to the frustration. Lesson #3 Once you start to notice the benefits from eating healthy, you\'ll wish you did it sooner. What motivates you? Remind yourself of that every day! If you have the desire to change, it\'s never too late. Once you learn the basics, practice &amp; get comfortable in the kitchen, you won\'t need to rely as much on following recipes by the book. You just have to start, experiment &amp; keep going because it\'ll be worth it! We\'ll explore cooking basics, preparing meals that you can make from whole foods, nutrient dense foods, \'supplementing\' with food, grocery shopping, food labels &amp; mindful eating. After that, we’ll jump into gardening &amp; growing food.\r\nThis is going to be fun !</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<table style=\"border-style: none;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr style=\"border-style: none;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 33%; text-align: center; text-justify: inter-word;\">Recipes</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 33%; text-align: center; text-justify: inter-word;\">Blog</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 33%; text-align: center; text-justify: inter-word;\">Videos</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"border-style: none;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 33%; text-align: center; text-justify: inter-word;\"><a href=\"http://localhost:8888/food-nut/welcome/page-pics-recipe-page/\"><img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-242\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/food-nut/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/Picture1-2-267x300.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"267\" height=\"300\" /></a></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 33%; text-align: center; text-justify