INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES("316", "1", "2017-05-27 21:48:30", "2017-05-27 21:48:30", "<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The Whole Food Nut Story</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-109 size-medium\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/food-nut/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/68016280-psdsc_8259_pp-200x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"200\" height=\"300\" />My health journey began about 12 years ago after multiple surgeries, debilitating pain &amp; consuming a very sad diet (standard american diet). I was working, living &amp; eating like most people....too much work, not much balance &amp; consuming processed food. At rock bottom &amp; determined to get better, a visit to Mayo Clinic ignited the change. I credit the physcians for helping me get started in a new direction by discussing integrative &amp; holistic options. Those recommendations have forever changed my life both personally &amp; professionally.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">I left a career in the pharmaceutical &amp; med device industry, started educating myself on how to eat (because I had no clue) &amp; pursued a Master\'s degree in nutrition. I was excited to be accepted into a new graduate nutrition program at the National University of Natural Medicine in Portland, OR.\r\nThere were so many advantages to learning in this environment surrounded by research, naturopathic &amp; oriental medicine students. Then there\'s the Portland factor that is ridiculously awesome in so many ways! From access to daily farmer\'s markets, to sustainability &amp; environmental consciousness, along with plenty of dairy, soy, nut &amp; gluten-free, non-GMO restaurants &amp; food trucks.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">So this Whole Food Nut went from consuming nothing but diet-coke, doritos &amp; <img class=\"alignright wp-image-114 size-thumbnail\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/food-nut/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/logotransparentbg-150x150.jpg\" alt=\"logotransparentbg\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" />iceberg lettuce to cooking &amp; preparing all of my meals. If it had no nutritonal value, I ate it. I literally didn\'t know how to boil an egg (no joke). Now I\'m a crazy nut in the kitchen who loves to experiment with new foods &amp; recipes while dancing to tunes. It\'s an endless science project.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">If you have the desire to change, it\'s never too late.  So grab your whole foods &amp; let\'s learn how to make healthy choices!</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"></p>", "About", "My health journey began about 12 years ago after multiple surgeries, debilitating pain &amp; consuming a very sad diet (standard american diet). I was working, living &amp; eating like most people....too much work, not much balance &amp; consuming processed food. At rock bottom &amp; determined to get better, a visit to Mayo Clinic ignited the change. I credit the physcians for helping me get started in a new direction by discussing integrative &amp; holistic options. Those recommendations have forever changed my life both personally &amp; professionally.", "inherit", "closed", "closed", "", "6-revision-v1", "", "", "2017-05-27 21:48:30", "2017-05-27 21:48:30", "", "6", "http://localhost:8888/food-nut/2017/05/27/6-revision-v1/", "0", "revision", "", "0");
