INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES("454", "1", "2017-06-13 22:30:29", "2017-06-13 22:30:29", "<table style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"float: right; width: 50%; text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-word;\">Wholefood Nut Tips</td>\r\n<td style=\"float: right; width: 50%; text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-word;\">Wholefood Nut Story</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<table style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"float: right; width: 50%; text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-word;\">I’m a Nutritionist &amp; Whole Food Nut that wants to help others overcome the hurdles to eating healthy. Thru educational videos, nutrition tips &amp; the Facebook page, I’ll share the health benefits of preparing &amp; eating whole foods. People are overwhelmed with the mass amount of conflicting &amp; rapidly changing nutrition data. I want to simplify &amp; break down the challenges to healthy eating as well as provide wellness &amp; nutrition tips to incorporate into your daily life. I’m not a fan of fad diets that promote one way of eating over another because every person has different nutritive needs that are based upon their biochemical individuality. Healthy eating is a balance of moderation &amp; variation not deprivation. There’s so many foods to discover, eat &amp; enjoy!<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-183\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/food-nut/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/Butterfly-pic-300x170.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"500\" height=\"283\" align=\"left\" /></td>\r\n<td style=\"float: right; width: 50%; text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-word;\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-183\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/food-nut/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/Butterfly-pic-300x170.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"500\" height=\"283\" align=\"right\" /> My health journey began about 12 years ago after multiple surgeries, debilitating pain & consuming a very sad diet (standard american diet).  I was working, living & eating like most people....too much work, not much balance & consuming processed food.  At rock bottom & determined to get better, a visit to Mayo Clinic ignited the change.  I credit the physcians for helping me get started in a new direction by discussing integrative & holistic options.  Those recommendations have forever changed my life both personally & professionally.\r\n \r\n\r\n </td>\r\n</tr>\r\n\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<table style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"float: right; width: 50%; text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-word;\">I’m a Nutritionist &amp; Whole Food Nut that wants to help others overcome the hurdles to eating healthy. Thru educational videos, nutrition tips &amp; the Facebook page, I’ll share the health benefits of preparing &amp; eating whole foods. People are overwhelmed with the mass amount of conflicting &amp; rapidly changing nutrition data. I want to simplify &amp; break down the challenges to healthy eating as well as provide wellness &amp; nutrition tips to incorporate into your daily life. I’m not a fan of fad diets that promote one way of eating over another because every person has different nutritive needs that are based upon their biochemical individuality. Healthy eating is a balance of moderation &amp; variation not deprivation. There’s so many foods to discover, eat &amp; enjoy!<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-183\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/food-nut/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/Butterfly-pic-300x170.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"500\" height=\"283\" align=\"left\" /></td>\r\n<td style=\"float: right; width: 50%; text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-word;\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-183\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/food-nut/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/Butterfly-pic-300x170.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"500\" height=\"283\" align=\"right\" />I left a career in the pharmaceutical & med device industry, started educating myself on how to eat (because I had no clue) & pursued a Master\'s degree in nutrition. I was excited to be accepted into a new graduate nutrition program at the National University of Natural Medicine in Portland, OR. \r\nThere were so many advantages to learning in this environment surrounded by research, naturopathic & oriental medicine students. Then there\'s the Portland factor that is ridiculously awesome in so many ways!  From access to daily farmer\'s markets, to sustainability & environmental consciousness, along with plenty of dairy, soy, nut & gluten-free, non-GMO restaurants & food trucks. \r\n \r\n </td>\r\n</tr>\r\n\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<table style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"float: right; width: 50%; text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-word;\">I’m a Nutritionist &amp; Whole Food Nut that wants to help others overcome the hurdles to eating healthy. Thru educational videos, nutrition tips &amp; the Facebook page, I’ll share the health benefits of preparing &amp; eating whole foods. People are overwhelmed with the mass amount of conflicting &amp; rapidly changing nutrition data. I want to simplify &amp; break down the challenges to healthy eating as well as provide wellness &amp; nutrition tips to incorporate into your daily life. I’m not a fan of fad diets that promote one way of eating over another because every person has different nutritive needs that are based upon their biochemical individuality. Healthy eating is a balance of moderation &amp; variation not deprivation. There’s so many foods to discover, eat &amp; enjoy!<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-183\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/food-nut/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/Butterfly-pic-300x170.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"500\" height=\"283\" align=\"left\" /></td>\r\n<td style=\"float: right; width: 50%; text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-word;\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-183\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/food-nut/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/Butterfly-pic-300x170.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"500\" height=\"283\" align=\"right\" />So this Whole Food Nut went 