INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES("626", "1", "2017-07-12 00:38:06", "2017-07-12 00:38:06", "<h3>Whole Food Nut Story</h3>\r\n<div class=\"about-page-block\">\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-567 size-medium alignleft\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/food-nut/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/WFN-Pro-Pics-About-Page-6-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" />\r\n\r\nLike many, I was living neither a healthy nor a harmonious lifestyle; too much work, not enough balance and processed food had caught up with me: in other words, CRAP (Chemicals, Refined Sugars, Additives and Preservatives).  The consequences of my sad diet (Standard American Diet) were piling up and my health was rapidly deteriorating: I had debilitating pain, followed by multiple surgeries and I was feeling like someone had a voodoo doll with my name on it. What the Health?!\r\n</div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div class=\"about-page-block\">\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-601 size-medium alignleft\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/food-nut/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/pexels-photo-423335-300x200.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" />\r\n\r\nDetermined to get better, a visit to Mayo Clinic finally ignited the change. It was my introduction to integrative and holistic medicine and I am forever grateful. Those recommendations changed my life both personally and professionally. I left a career in pharma/med device, started educating myself on how to eat and eventually pursued a master’s degree in nutrition at the National University of Natural Medicine, an excellent educational program with a blend of naturopathic and oriental medicine, research and global health students. Even better, the school was in Portland, Oregon, a ridiculously awesome city in so many ways. We had daily access to farmer’s markets, a heightened awareness for sustainability and engaging with the environment, not to mention a host of insanely healthy restaurants and food trucks.\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"about-page-block\">\r\n<p align=\"justify\"><img class=\"wp-image-596 size-medium alignleft\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/food-nut/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/test-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" /></p>\r\nThis Whole Food Nut went from consuming Diet Coke, Doritos &amp;amp; iceberg lettuce (if it had no nutritional value, I ate it), to preparing all my meals. I literally did not know how to boil an egg (no yoke), and now I’m a crazy food nut who loves to experiment with whole foods and healthy recipes. Now that I’ve shared my journey to good health, I hope you will join me. Bring a sense of humor, a healthy dose of patience and let’s get healthy!\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h3 align=\"justify\">Whole Food Nut Tips</h3>\r\n<div class=\"about-page-block\">\r\n\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-603 size-medium alignleft\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/food-nut/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/pexels-photo-111112-300x202.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"202\" />\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 2.2em; text-align: left;\" align=\"justify\">I’m a Nutritionist &amp; Whole Food Nut that wants to help others overcome the hurdles to eating healthy. Thru educational videos, nutrition tips &amp; the Facebook page, I’ll share the health benefits of preparing &amp; eating whole foods. People are overwhelmed with the mass amount of conflicting &amp; rapidly changing nutrition data. I want to simplify &amp; break down the challenges to healthy eating as well as provide wellness &amp; nutrition tips to incorporate into your daily life. I’m not a fan of fad diets that promote one way of eating over another because every person has different nutritive needs that are based upon their biochemical individuality.Healthy eating is a balance of moderation &amp; variation not deprivation.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"about-page-block\">\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-600 size-medium alignleft\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/food-nut/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/pexels-photo-262918-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\" align=\"justify\">There’s so many foods to discover, eat &amp; enjoy! Where do I begin? What should I eat? What the heck is a whole food? After hearing these questions asked over &amp; over, I reflected on my food journey &amp; realized the need for food education. We are not taught in school one of the most important things in life; what &amp; how to eat. It’s not pretty when I reflect on my initial attempts at cooking &amp; learning what to eat. Lesson #1 This doesn’t happen overnight. Be patient, have a good sense of humor &amp; embrace your kitchen as a science experiment! Lesson #2 Do not start with fancy recipes because that will only add to the frustration. Lesson #3 Once you start to notice the benefits from eating healthy, you’ll wish you did it sooner.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"about-page-block\">\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-591 size-medium alignleft\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/food-nut/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/pexels-photo-196643-300x200.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\" align=\"justify\">What motivates you? Remind yourself of that every day! If you have the desire to change, it’s never too late. Once you learn the basics, practice &amp; get comfortable in the kitchen, you won’t need to rely as much on following recipes by the book. You just need to start, experiment &amp; keep going because it’ll be worth it! We’ll explore cooking basics, preparing meals with whole foods, nutrient dense foods, ‘supplementing’ with food, grocery shopping, food labels, mindful eating and gardening.</p>\r\n</div>", "About", "My health journey began about 12 years ago after multiple surgeries, debilitating pain &amp; consuming a very sad diet (standard american diet). I was working, living &amp; eating like most people....too much work, not much balance &amp; consuming processed food. At rock bottom &amp; determined to get better, a visit to Mayo Clinic ignited the change. I credit the physcians for helping me get started in a new direction by discussing integrative &amp; holistic options. Those recommendations have forever changed my life both personally &amp; professionally.", "inherit", "closed", "closed", "", "6-revision-v1", "", "", "2017-07-12 00:38:06", "2017-07-12 00:38:06", "", "6", "http://localhost:8888/food-nut/2017/07/12/6-revision-v1/", "0", "revision", "", "0");
